## Dev-2 Contribution — Patient & Appointment Modules

### New Files Added

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `app/Repositories/PatientRepository.php` | Raw SQL for patients table (create, list, find, update, soft delete) |
| `app/Repositories/AppointmentRepository.php` | Raw SQL for appointments table (create, list, find, update, date range) |
| `app/Services/PatientService.php` | Business logic for patient CRUD (tenant validation, duplicate profile check) |
| `app/Services/AppointmentService.php` | Business logic for appointments (conflict check, patient role auto-derive) |
| `app/Controllers/PatientController.php` | HTTP layer for patient routes (reads input, validates, calls service) |
| `app/Controllers/AppointmentController.php` | HTTP layer for appointment routes (reads input, validates, calls service) |

### Modified Files

| File | What Changed |
|------|-------------|
| `app/Routes/api.php` | Added `routeWithId()` for dynamic `{id}` routes, registered all 8 new endpoints, fixed `$basePath` |
| `app/Middleware/CsrfMiddleware.php` | Added new routes to exclude list, fixed `$basePath`, added trailing `/id` strip logic |

---

### Endpoints Added

#### Patient Management

| Method | Endpoint | Roles | Description |
|--------|----------|-------|-------------|
| POST | `/patients` | Doctor, Nurse | Create patient profile linked to an existing user |
| GET | `/patients` | Doctor, Nurse | List all non-deleted patients in the tenant |
| PUT | `/patients/{id}` | Doctor, Nurse | Partial update — only sends fields change |
| DELETE | `/patients/{id}` | Doctor, Nurse | Soft delete — sets `deleted_at`, record stays in DB |

#### Appointment & Calendar

| Method | Endpoint | Roles | Description |
|--------|----------|-------|-------------|
| POST | `/appointments` | Doctor, Nurse, Patient | Create appointment with conflict validation |
| GET | `/appointments` | Doctor, Nurse, Patient | List appointments (patient sees only their own) |
| PUT | `/appointments/{id}` | Doctor, Nurse | Update status, notes, or reschedule |
| GET | `/calendar?from=&to=` | All roles | Fetch appointments by date range |

---

### Key Design Decisions

**Tenant isolation** — every query filters by `tenant_id` from the JWT payload. No client input is trusted for tenant.

**Soft delete** — `DELETE /patients/{id}` sets `deleted_at = NOW()`. Every SELECT and UPDATE filters `WHERE deleted_at IS NULL`, so deleted records are invisible without being removed from the DB.

**Conflict validation** — `POST /appointments` checks for same `doctor_id + appointment_date + tenant_id` where status is not `cancelled` before inserting. Returns `409 Conflict` if a slot is taken.

**Patient role auto-derive** — when a user with role `patient` creates an appointment, `patient_id` is looked up from the `patients` table using their `user_id` from the JWT. They cannot spoof another patient's ID.

**Partial update** — `PUT /patients/{id}` uses `array_key_exists()` to merge incoming fields with existing data, so sending only `{"address": "Chennai"}` updates only address without nulling out other fields.

**CSRF exclusion** — new API routes are JWT-protected (stateless), so they are excluded from session-based CSRF checks in `CsrfMiddleware`. Auth is handled entirely by `AuthMiddleware::handle()` + `allowRoles()`.


